						               													<description>Complete MagicSoccer Card Game&amp;#10;Created and illustrated by Alessandro Dolcetta&amp;#10;&amp;#10;It is a complete deck of cards composed of&amp;#10;36 Offensive Cards&amp;#10;36 defensive Cards&amp;#10;8 Team cards&amp;#10;5 Ball Cards&amp;#10;2 Yellow Cards&amp;#10;4 Red Cards&amp;#10;1 Rule sheet&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The game is a funny simulation of a Soccer match, played by Wizards, that with their Spells Cards try to advance the ball onto the opposite net to score a Goal. &amp;#10;First who score two Goals wins or you can play by time.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;It is an easy game where offensive and defensive player, play simultaneously their Card. Depending on the position on the field (formed by 16 cards)you match different combos that may be a dribbling, a shoot, an interception, a corner or... a goal!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Cards are easy to read: they just report the name of the offensive or defensive spells (in Latin) and the number power of that spell.&amp;#10;The different colours of the cards background greatly help to recognize each of them when you have your hand of 11 cards.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Very good for children, for the coloured &amp;quot;comics&amp;quot; illustrations, and families that wish to relax with a simple, easy game.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;On the Author website&amp;#10;www.alex-games.com&amp;#10;find plenty of info also in english, pictures and descriptions.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Wizards of Soccer will be present at &amp;#10;Angelo Porazzi Games Booth 9-30 Essen 2008&amp;#10;with English rulesheet&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
